SIMPLE: curtail
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Curtail
<hw>Cur*tail"</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucr⟧r*t⟦amac⟧l")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Curtailed</conjf>
<pr>(-t⟦amac⟧ld")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Curtailing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See <er>Curtal</er>.]</ety>
<def>To cut off the end or tail, or any part, of; to shorten; to
abridge; to diminish; to reduce.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I, that am <qex>curtailed</qex> of this fair proportion.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our incomes have been <qex>curtailed</qex>; his salary has been
doubled.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Curtail</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Curtail
<hw>Cur"tail</hw> <pr>(k?r"t?l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The scroll
termination of any architectural member, as of a step, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Curtail dog</ent>⟦br⟧
